secrets-thumbdriver


Overview
--------

Creates a disk-image file (image-secrets) within the current directory
which is GUID-partitioned with a single LUKS-encrypted partition.
You may then `dd` this file to a series of thumb-drives.


How to use
----------

Clone this repo.

Place the secrets you wish to have encrypted into the 'payload' directory.

invoke `./secrets-thumbdriver`

`dd` the resultant 'image-secrets' disk-image file to a device of your choice,
for example:

sudo dd if=image-secrets of=/dev/sda status=progress ; sudo sync
